articles.author: David Shepardson
articles.description: The U.S. Federal Aviation Administration said on Wednesday night that a PSA Airlines regional jet collided midair with a Sikorsky H-60 helicopter while on approach to Reagan Washington National Airport.
articles.title: Regional jet collides with helicopter near Washington's Reagan Airport

articles.author: Saurabh Sharma, Shivam Patel
articles.description: Police said 30 people were killed in the crush at the world's biggest gathering of humanity, but sources told Reuters the death toll was nearly 40.
articles.title: India orders probe into Kumbh festival stampede that killed dozens

articles.author: Jeff Mason, Andrea Shalal, Andy Sullivan
articles.description: President Donald Trump's administration pulled back a proposed spending freeze that threatened to disrupt hundreds of billions of dollars in aid to U.S. programs, a White House official said on Wednesday.
articles.title: White House revokes spending freeze in face of legal challenges

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Dawoud Abu Alkas
articles.description: The joy of thousands of Palestinian families who made it back home in north Gaza after a ceasefire with Israel is turning to despair as the cold reality of uninhabitable, bombed-out homes and dire shortages of basic supplies sets in.
articles.title: Joy turns to despair as Gaza returnees struggle to settle in enclave's north

articles.author: Shoon Naing, Devjyot Ghoshal
articles.description: Four years after seizing power in a dawn coup that ousted an elected civilian government, Myanmar's embattled ruling generals are making their most concerted effort to gain legitimacy - by pushing to hold another election.
articles.title: Risk of violence escalates in Myanmar's civil war as junta flags elections

articles.author: Yassin Kombi, Sonia Rolley
articles.description: Rwandan-backed M23 rebels appeared to have consolidated their control over Goma, with eastern Congo's largest city mostly quiet on Wednesday apart from sporadic gunfire in some outlying districts, residents said.
articles.title: Congo's M23 rebels consolidate control over a devastated Goma

articles.author: Laila Kearney
articles.description: A law firm representing victims of the Eaton Fire in Los Angeles has submitted photos with a legal filing on Wednesday that appear to show exposed wire at the base of a Southern California Edison tower that the firm alleges may have contributed to the deadly blaze.
articles.title: Exposed utility wires may have contributed to LA's Eaton Fire, law firm says

articles.author: Jeff Mason
articles.description: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Wednesday he will order the Pentagon and the Department of Homeland Security to prepare a migrant facility at Guantanamo Bay for as many as 30,000 migrants.
articles.title: Trump to prepare facility at Guantanamo for 30,000 migrants

articles.author: Renju Jose, Christine Chen
articles.description: Israel urged Australia to do more to halt an "epidemic of antisemitism" in the country as Prime Minister Anthony Albanese said his government was doing all it could to combat attacks that he says include domestic terrorism.
articles.title: Australia's Albanese defends antisemitism response as Israel urges more action

articles.author: Michelle Nichols, Dan Burns
articles.description: The U.S. Agency for International Development has told all aid groups to immediately pause all U.S.-funded programs "until further notice" as humanitarian groups grapple with a lack of clarity on waivers to President Donald Trump's 90-day aid pause.
articles.title: Aid groups get blanket order to pause U.S.-funded programs as payments dry up
